name: Cosmic Condo
description: When a boomer ship arrives in the present, its inhabitants are stunned to see how far life in space has come. So impressed that they seek to turn their own ship into a luxury living and leisure space. Can you help the rest of the galaxy get on board?
rules:
-- Unique Supply Missions are available during the event. Open the Event to access them.
-- Using Brunt, P. Mayweather, Donatra, Ferengi, or Romulans will provide a bonus to Supply Missions.
-- Every Supply Mission you complete earns you Event Victory Points. Collect Event Victory Points to unlock Threshold Rewards!
-- Community Rewards are only available during Phase 1. Collect Event Victory Points to unlock these rewards before the phase change!
-- In this event, Squadrons may also compete to advance up the Squadron leaderboards. Join a Squadron to get more rewards!
bonus_text: Crew Bonus: Brunt, P. Mayweather, Donatra, Ferengi, or Romulans
rewards_teaser: Reach Rank 1 by gaining Victory Points from Event Supply Missions!

featured_crew.name: Torres
featured_crew.flavor: While unconscious, Torres finds her mother aboard the Barge of the Dead, bound for Gre’Thor, the realm of the Klingon afterlife meant for dishonored souls.

goals.flavor: Fleece the competition with the Ferengi Alliance.
Fight the competition with the Ferengi Traditionalists.
Respect zoning laws with the Romulan Star Empire.

screens.text: "It was only a matter of time until more boomer ships from centuries ago made their way into the present. It's always exciting to see how they react to the way things have changed, but I have to say, this ship in particular is quick to adapt."

"They're talking about turning their generational ship into a luxury living and leisure space - one where people can shop and enjoy themselves as well as live. I have to hand it to them, it's pretty impressive. But..."
"...but its current location is inside the Romulan Neutral Zone. We have instructed the vessel to leave the area immediately or be treated as the security threat they are."

"Once they've resolved their little zoning issue, we can talk about their pricing. They've undercut every Ferengi establishment in the quadrant. Really, I'm saying this as an ally. You wouldn't want to deal with someone less diplomatic than I."
"As you can see, Captain, our new visitors could really use some help. I'm hoping you could give them some guidance."
